caption: Stopped by for just a light snack - got the fried cauliflower. Can't remember when I last had something so delectable. Excited to come back to try more!

Bistro781 is a young and lively place. It has a distinct decor and vibe to it. The service is good and fast. Folks are nice and welcoming. The food on the other side, has its limitations. The food in general lacks flavors and falls more on the bland side. The burger and tacos were dry and needed salt, some sauce for spice / flavor. Fries were super greasy. Their desserts are good but overall, the food quality, taste and the price point are quite mismatched. PS: the place is loud. Be prepared for that

Have been wanting to try and it was not a good experience! Did to go for my family my son popcorn chicken was not at all popcorn chicken it was just a big greasy messy. Fries were too hard to eat. I got the paella for myself, the scallops and shrimp were not cooked properly. The rice was so hard and salty after 2 bites my stomach started to turn. The cheese on my son pizza want even melted all the way: I really wanted to like this place but it’s a no for me.
I’m giving 3 stars because one of the employees which says he is the owner ( but he is not) even doesn’t know how to talk with customer.
Went for brunch and we were very impressed. The menu is great, I cant wait to go back and try more!
Had a excellent experience in this spot with my wife. The food came rapidly and the customer service is just great. Prices are reasonable.
Food was fulfilling.
Food, service, atmosphere, covid safety were all fantastic. Couldn't reccomend more.

The service was good and we immedieatly got the seats. However, the food as per the taste was not so good. Nothing wrong with the resturant, just did not like the taste of the ordered food and the cost was not worth for the same. Quantity of the food was also less.
Awesome food. Most things on the menu had a Gluten free version available, friendly staff, COVID safe.

I come to this special restaurant often since I enjoy the good mood that is part of this place. The personel is extremely loving and qualified. The service is exceptionally rapid. Also, the food they cook is perfect. I ate there many times and I was always delighted. The pay is decent. I highly recommend this restaurant to my friends and family.
Great food, super friendly employees, consistently good atmosphere. They charge reasonable rates and the food quality is great. 5 stars.
Great food. Been there multiple times. Girlfriend and I love it, along with both our families. Highly recommended.
Great food and drinks.
Good food, great cocktails.
Excellent food.

This place is my favorite. I eat in a lot of restaurants but here I  constantly return again and again. The crew is very helpful and the cooking they serve is so delicious. I would always prefer to have a nice meal in this restaurant. I highly recommend this place.
Amazing food and service! Waltham Gem!
This restaurant is amazing and broad, the meals was delightful and the prices were very reasonable. fast, effective service and very amiable waiters. I highly recommend this place.
Cute inside and offering outside seating. Menu us comprehensive and fairly priced.
The food legit has no taste. You ever taste a crab cake that tastes more like an herb garden then crab? Go here to experience it.

I love Bistro 781.  Great, food, drinks and atmosphere.  I have been here for events, girls nights, dinners, lunch and it is organized and the staff is so nice!   It is always a go to restaurant in for me.  Recently my daughter has gone gluten free and dairy free which is hard for a teenager and  they are very accommodating when we have ordered take out and dined here.  Just being able to take her to a restaurant and know she can eat a variety of foods means the world to us!  Thank you Bistro for a great experience!

Good spot to grab a bite right in Moody St. The restaurant space itself was nice (beautiful large bar) and was setup well inside for COVID prevention along with offering outdoor seating. Our server was nice albeit not very attentive. The food was good, with the star being the poutine app. Overall a good spot.
(Translated by Google) It is a very nice atmosphere and delicious food  (Original) Es muy agradable anviente y rica comida

Not all the outdoor tables have umbrellas so we got caught out in the mid-day sun. The food was very slow to come. The pork belly in the pork belly tacos was not at all tender, and they weren't very filling.

This is our favorite breakfast spot in town. Pat is so friendly and really, just makes me miss my grandma! :) The food is always fresh and hot, and the coffee is bottomless. The mugs are great, too - good old classic cafe mugs, we may have to ask to buy one next time we visit. There is usually a line on weekends, but they move people in quickly and the service doesn't feel rushed at all. We look forward to breakfast so much when weave Pat's on the agenda!

I was there for the first time. I enjoyed the live music. that as the only good thing. If you are short on staff don't try just fill the tables. we shouldn't have to wave to the waitress to get attention so have to come to  our table. We didn't see her anymore after she took our order. Nobody came to our table to see if we may need refill on our drinks. we had to ask for our bill from somebody who came to get our plates. Home fries were old. I can understand it was busy but you can't cook something and put ir on the side for all day. We have a family take out place and usually I go to new places to see what is going on in food industry, I know when sth is not fresh. people work for their money, you should work to earn it too.
I very much enjoy the dishes and customer service, fantastic location next to my home. The employees are always nice. Would recommend to others.
Awesome!
Indoor and outdoor seating. Excellent service. The food was delicious. Six different meals ordered and we loved everything.

I've been there twice and absolutely enjoy the short rib mac n cheese.  The raw oysters however must be farmed raised.  They have 0 taste of the ocean they are from and they also have a not so fresh scent.  Enjoy everything else but stay away from the oysters.
Decent food, cool atmosphere but expensive for the quality.
A little slow out of the kitchen at lunchtime today for a table of 4, but the food was really good.
Love the food, outdoor sitting area and the drinks. Perfect place for weekend brunch.
This restaurant is awesome and broad, the menu was yummy and the prices were very affordable. quickly, productive service and very personal staff. Highly recommended.
Great food and environment. It’s a great place to go to to have a nice dinner with friends or a date or get drinks. Food is high quality and so is the whole restaurant itself. I strongly recommend it

two days ago was our first time we visited this fine restaurant. But It is no doubt not the last. We had a good time with the excellent service, with the first-rate  cuisine and booze and with the comfortable cost. We will absolutely return there in a short time.
Food is good, ambiance is better but service is not good
A nice place on moody st. Great food and service. Lots of GF options and vegan as well.
High price with super service. Not coming back
Sat outside with social distancing. Food was delicious!

Was planning to dine here, and came through a back entrance and was going about 10 mph over a gigantic speed bump when a waitress stepped right in front of my car and yelled, “Slow down, slow down!” She then proceeded to go behind my car and hit it with her hand. Did not even want to deal with this if that’s the nature of their staff so we dined elsewhere.
Tuna poke bowl and chicken fettuccine were delicious

Service was good. Waitress was friendly and offered a couple variations of fries. Food was a little bland, but prices were reasonable, so I'll go back and give something else a shot. Edit: I had the Crunch wrap burger.
Good food and friendly staff!
The bloody mary alone is sufficient reason to go

Food was amazing. Weather was great. Tables both in the front and around back in the shade. This is the most gluten-friendly place I've found in the Greater Boston area. Service was a little slow, but given the circumstances of new cleanliness standards, I'd say they did great. If its on the menu, I recommend the vegan avocado cake.
The food and atmosphere was exceptional. They have outdoor seating now!
Too many home fries and not enough veggies in my veggie dish. Would like to have seen more diversity is visible staff.
Good ambience
Solid spot, one of the only ones on this busy street that was open during our trip here. Lobster bisque was amazing. Oysters were great also. Overall great experience.
Outdoor seating worked well with Moody St blocked off and nice weather. The scallop entree I had for dinner was excellent.

Very impressed with the quality of food and service during the Pandemic. I felt safe on my very first time eating out. A lot of switching to paper/plastic goods, which, honestly, is way cleaner. Spacing inside and out is more than acceptable for distancing. All in all. This was a make it or break it outing for me and Bistro781 made this a great experience.
Best restaurant in Waltham! Cannot wait to go back!
Excellent food and service. Wait staff is fun and engaging! Highly recommend.

The service was amazing! Daniella was our server and she was so good with checking on us and getting our drinks fast, mind you there was 8 of us on a busy Friday night! There was live music from 9:30 to 11/12 and it was an awesome reggae band. The steak frite with fries was delicious as well as the spinach and artichoke dip. 10/10 would recommend!
Stellar service and delicious food. Lots of vegetarian and gluten-free options. Will definitely return!
Food was awesome
A little slow on service at lunch time. However lots of choices and the food was excellent. They also have a vegan & vegetarian menu, just ask your server!
Food was delicious and service was amazing. The hosts were able to seat us very quickly despite it being a busy Sunday brunch.
Duck hash. 🦆
Good drinks
It was obvious the waitress spilled my drink and she made no attempt to own to it.

It was my favorite restaurant in the town, my husband and I really enjoy their food before. Before I will have a long time leave Boston, we spent our last brunch here. I ordered the zucchini bread as I always do However I was not lucky, they made me disappointed. After my next table had their second zucchini bread and all the people in my table get their food, I still did not get my food. I asked the waitress, and she told me it was canceled. It was confused, but I finally get it. But it is not the bread as usual, the dough was dry and edge still was maybe uncooked throughly, just  dry and hard. Even the fork can not make it cut easily. It was also thinner than before and thinner than the two bread on my next table. I understand the size is varied every time, but just wish it can be normal quality and quantity, because it will be a long time I can not have it.  They apologized for these, maybe next they will be back to the normal. Anyway, it is a good restaurant, they provide good food most time. Maybe I am just not lucky this time, hope I can be lucky next time.

I think I'm in l❤️ve.  Amazing comfort food.  I can't single out one item on the menu.  Everything we tried was delicious.   Thank you to our kind and friendly waitress for making the night fun and stress-free.  She handled a table of 10 like a pro!

A lively place. Many seats at the bar. Good menu variety. Healthy choices too including vegan and vegetarian, but plenty of hearty meat meals too. Great place. Nice popular music playing. They also have live entertainment at 9pm on weekends.
Nice place. Food was good.
Went here for lunch and it was good all around

place is awesome, staff is awesome, atmosphere is great, crazy menu, very different from most restaurants. Their brunch is awesome. You have to try: short rib sandwich and short rib hash on the brunch menu, banana bread french toast, zucchini bread, the thick cut bacon is bonkers, their cocktails are awesome. My favorite place on Moody St, and their are tons of good spots on Moody. Dinner menu is unreal, the seafood dishes are the best.
The frittata was delicious and the pancakes fluffy. Definitely coming back for brunch
Bloody Mary's are great!
Great vegan menu!
Salads are fantastic!

Bistro is a go to in Waltham. Casey is the GREATEST bartender in Massachusetts, crafting the best Espresso Martinis this side of the Rocky Mountains, heck this side of the Sierra Nevadas. Don't sleep on the oysters, gnocchi, or Lobster Mac & Cheese. You won't be disappointed at Bistro 781

My wife and I went for brunch. Overall it was totally worth checking out. Interesting menu, whether you want a more traditional meal like an omelet or something a tad more frisky, they have a nice variety of brunch options. And the brunch cocktails are nice! If you like coffee cocktails or a ridiculously customizable Bloody Mary, this is your place.
It was lit are waitress was dope 🤣
Really good food on the late night menu
Very yummy food in an energetic environment. We will be back!
Great food.  Great people.  What more can you ask for!
Very accommodating. Good brunch place for larger groups. Breakfast burrito and breakfast sandwich are both very good. Didn’t have the largest drink menu but they did what they did very well.
Very busy and understaffed on November 3rd for brunch. Had to ask for refills consistently on my drink. Food was amazing and server was nice!

Food was delicious. I had chicken corn  and my husband had steak frites. Very tasty and the servers were very friendly. It took a while to get the food but then we went on a super busy Sunday afternoon!!!! 🙂
The food was decent - not terrible, but the price and flavor didn't match up. The drinks were way overpriced for what I got (had three old fashions that had an ice cube nearly the size of the glass).
Very noisy, food poorly prepared and unimaginative
Nice place
Service was great, but the food wasn't too good. Very pricy
Rude bar staff mostly ruined the whole experience
Fantastic  brunch. Service is exceptional and the Bloodymary is a most❤
Great spot plus off street parking. Huge for moody st.
Food was delicious,  live music was very good, great atmosphere.

The chef's dishes are extremely well thought out and every component on the plate was fantastic. This place is a gem for sure. Our server was also very knowledgeable about food allergies and we had no issues with gluten cross contamination (celiac). Love this place!
Great service at the bar.  You can also order from the full menu.  All you really need is one of the Bistro bloody Mary's.  Mine had a pepperoni pizza and a seared scallop!
Food just fair. Noisy. Bad acoustics for normal conversation hearing. Not a pleasant evening overall.
Got a breakfast burrito and wife got a Benedict sandwich with duck hash. Fantastic meals!!!

Real Bistros are few and far between. 781 nails it. Good interesting approachable food and great selection of wines. I had oysters, fresh and we'll presented. Tuna poke followed. Absolute winner! Great balance of flavor and texture. Delicious tuna and perfectly cooked rice "cake" combined with perfectly balanced sauces. Highly recommend.
Cider mule is so smooth it's ridiculous. Had the duck and it was so tender. Highly recommend.
Typical Boston attitude Food ok
Food was amazing for what I had expected. I will admit I went in with a low bar and was impressed. The gluten free food was very good too.

Amazing food. I'm from the UK and went with my colleague Pat. I loved the food. We the Ham and Calamari for starters and Had the Panini and Burger between us and boy is was so delicious.  Highly recommended. Portions were big also.

What an awesome place! I had the Tuna tacos with a side of the Mexican street corn. The tuna in the tacos was soft and flavorful. Paired with the chili slaw, this is a must-try. The hard shell was thin and crispy, but not the type that falls apart in your hands while eating it. The Mexican street corn is pulled straight off the cob, meaning the kernels are firm and sweet. I’ll be coming back to see what other tasty offerings are on their menu!
The Mexican Street corn is a must have. All the food was delicious and fresh! There service also handled our larger party with ease.
It said veal chop on the menu, but it was a pork chop.
Atmosphere. Quick service. Food. All great.
They offer amazing brunch options.  The bloody Mary's are the best!!! Great service and a good experience over all.
excellent food excellent service
Food was good, but they didn't charge the price listed on the menu.
Went there for a birthday and got great service, great cocktails, and wonderful food. Would recommend a revisit. We will be going back hopefully
Great food, great service! Thanks Elena!
This place has a great gluten free menu
Fries are great

We came for brunch, but once I saw the tuna tacos on the menu, I had to get them. They were so perfect, the cabbage was a nice crunch and the taco shell was perfectly crisp. They serve coke products and had an extensive brunch menu. The atmosphere was relaxed and sports games were playing on the tv.

Place was a little loud to carry a proper conversation. We started with the artichoke dip but were not very impressed. I ordered the tuna tacos (shown in pic), they were tasty but on the small side. My friend ordered the short ribs tacos which were far better.
Wait staff should pay attention to their customers instead of socializing- have no idea where the manager was

My wife and I went to the restaurant about 6:30 to avoid the crowd. We sat at a high top table across from the bar. After sitting for 15 minutes we finally got waited on   The blonde waitress after having a great conversation with another table of people I think she knew finally came over and said are you drinking anything besides water. Then we ordered two Stella’s but asked if we could get a frosted glass like a customer that was drinking a cold beer beside us. She then proceeded to tell us that we couldn’t if because that Stella only came in it’s own style glass. I said I can’t get a frosted mug for a beer ? She said no and was starting to argue with us. Then she said let me check by then I was saying I’m going to have this kind of experience over a frosted beer glass for 10 dollars what’s my experience going to be with a 150 dollar dinner. Bad experience bad wait staff no manager no regard for customers. Just go there and open the front door throw 200 dollars cash on the floor and walk out you’re going to have a better experience that way.

A great find, for us. We could've gone to places we knew, but instead we branched out to Bistro 781. Great menu. It was really hard to decide. Draft beer selection very good. Staff so friendly. Would most definitely go again.
Great atmosphere, sophisticated and laid back, great for any occasion.
Elena gives the best recommendations! And she remembers us every time. The food and drinks are consistently good
Killer breakfast sandwich.
The staff was outstanding and very accommodating when we had to wait for some time for our table. The food was also excellent.

Great dining experience overall. The food (I got the steak frites) was amazing. The truffle fries were a little overcooked but that did not take away from the experience. The service was good, not great and the beers on tap were very limited. I would most likely return to Bistro781 on the future.
The vegan/vegetarian menu rocks, for that alone 5 stars.
The food there is amazing

Great food and ambience! A treasure on Moody St. The staff is wonderfully friendly and the food is delicious! Plus, they are the only restaurant (aside from Masao's which is all vegan) with a vegan menu on Moody St! Very delicious and inclusive. A local favorite.
Good service
Had dinner here recently and it was a nice space with friendly staff and the food was really good!  I would definitely come here again.

This review is for brunch only. We went on fathers day right when they opened and they sat a lot of people at the same time so it took a bit for things to settle but once they did every thing was wonderful. Staff was on point and friendly. We ended up trying thr make your own bloody mary. A little expensive but worth it just for the fun of it. The bloody mary wasn't the best tasting it needed more spice. I got the eggs Benedict with short rib hash. The portion was huge. It was delicious. Our son got a kids meal and again the portion was great. We will definitely be back.

Our server Erin was fantastic. She was knowledgeable and incredibly pleasant. Great customer service. Delicious food, really great drinks...try the Hot-n-Dirty martini. You will love! The short rib mac and cheese was outstanding. Love this place.
Food tasted good, but I got extremely gluten sick.
Amazing Food!!

Go to Waltham once every few months and Bistro is the only reason why. The place is incredible from top to bottom. The food is always amazing. I’ve had several different servers and they were all equally great. The owner makes time to come out and meet guests. It’s hands down one of the best spots in and around Boston!
Food was fantastic ,staff was super friendly,helpful and extremely efficient.  A new favorite for our family.
The food, the music and the services.  Good people.

I went here for Sunday brunch, I had the smoked salmon, ginger slaw, wasabi cream cheese (get the wasabi cream cheese on the side so you can add the amount you can tolerate) sandwich, and it was FANTASTIC! The service was good, I had tea on this visit but generally the drinks here are always made well, the cocktail flavors are unique and tasty, the restaurant is allergy sensitive/tolerant. I'd defo recommend bistro781
THE REAL DEAL... EXCELLENT STAFF EXCELLENT FOOD SERVICE ETC, I PROMISE YOU, TELL THEM I SENT YOU... JERRY WHAT'S GOOD...💪🏾
If you're in Waltham, have lunch or brunch here. Great food.
Jeff and the staff at Bistro were fabulous helping to organize my son’s graduation party. The food was delicious and service outstanding!! Thank you!

I'm not familiar with the area but chatting with the concierge girl (who was changing the menu outside and was saying all food is soooo good here) made it easy to decide to pop in. There were no tables available so headed to the bar, ordered a burger without bun. It was all okay, but very greasy for my taste.  The truffle fries would have been awesome but they were soggy from the oil.  Same for the burger which was probably just put on straight from the frying pan making the lettuce soaking in oil too... Maybe you get different stuff at the bar not sure but it is really not a place to return for food. However the 3 star is for the staff.  I did not get cutleries and when I asked from a waitress (who clearly should not helping me out at the bar) had no issues to drop everything and give me a set. The bartender who took my order (then I think he went for a break or finished his shift and the girls who replaced him did not show interest in checking on me though) was sweet remembered all details of the order; the concierge girl was sweet and enthusiastic about the place so I still think that this is a good place or one with potential.
Good food and nice place!
Great food. Got the Cubano and the duck breast with risotto. Both were great. Service was fast.
Great brunch spot, menu has a lot of options for food and drink. Different kinds of mimosas available. Weekends get busy so I would recommend a reservation in advance!
Great place for brunch.  While it's on the pricey side, I have never been disappointed in a meal here.  Bar has full menu service as well, so if you can't get a table the bar is always an option.
The prosciutto wrapped watermelon and the tacos were great. The filet was a bit overcooked and the scalloped potatoes were just ok.
Good food, not too expensive. Probably best for brunch, as it's the bulk of their menu, but we went there for lunch - which was still really good.

Loved the short rib tacos, cauliflower tacos, and brussel sprout tacos. The only thing I didn't like was there noise level; the room had no noise dampening so I couldn't even talk to the other people at my table.
Innovative

Best food in Waltham! Just visiting the area, but went here twice and tried five different dishes. Everything was amazing, fresh, and creative! Beautiful presentation of food that out shines much more expensive restaurants in the area. Staff is super friendly, helpful, and attentive! Highly recommend!
This place is great! We recently tried it for the first time with friends, we had several apps, several different cocktails, and 3 entrees, and everything was fantastic.
Shrimp and Grits, a lot of food, couldn't finish it but I wanted to. Friendly  service, clean, all the check boxes were met.
Good brunch but not a good place to be on a busy night. An hour sitting at the table until food arrived. Given the excellent choices within a 3 minute walk, I doubt I'll be back.
Great food and local beers as usual. And now they have historic pictures of Waltham on the walls!

Nice restaurant with a dedicated vegan/vegetarian menu (just ask!). I had the cauliflower tacos and they were incredible but the portion sizes are smaller. Definitely got noisy and the wait staff kept asking to take our plates while we were still working on our food (3 or 4 times over a 30 minute period).

A little a little pricey scallop dinner with a bear $ 40 you get three pieces of scallops and I don't know what kind of vegetable that is I think it's artichoke maybe I don't know and on a bed of rice something like that was not really rice though it was a little pricey but it was delicious I chowed it but wish they had added more scallops
You can't beat the $1 oysters. But they have a good food selection, and the restaurant has a cool vibe. I'll definitely be back.
Great as always. Been a semi regular there for a few years. Big tip ask for the chimichurri.
Very friendly staff, food is good, a bit pricey, but tasty!

Amazing Brunch! Best chicken pot pie I have ever tasted. I highly recommend you make a reservation because of their outrageous wait times on the weekend but it is worth it and the staff was super nice and courteous.
Great Drinks. Great food

Nice atmosphere, REALLY enjoyed the beer, the food quality and price ratio seemed off. I ordered the steak frites and I could tell a cheap grade was used for the meat. Fries tasted good but were on the mushy side as far as texture was concerned ... No complaints on the broccoli. I'm fewer words, the staff was friendly and the atmosphere/decor was very pleasant, I just expected better quality food for the price we paid.
Hostess and waitress were amazingly nice . Food was not fresh at all. I had the tacos very disappointed in the quality and freshness of the food.  Broccoli was cold.
Great gluten free options.  Tasty drinks
Awesome date spot for the over 40 crowd

Went for brunch with my girlfriend and her mom. It was so loud we could barely hear each other and when i asked the manager if he could turn the music down a bit, he was very nice and polite but said he couldn't because of the owner.  My sandwich was delicious (it's the chicken pesto, would definitely recommend), but my girlfriend ordered brussel sprout tacos and got 2 tiny tacos with no protein for $14, which is a bit ridiculous. Her mom got a flavorless salad for a similar price.  Even though i enjoyed my meal, I wouldn't go back because the noisiness was so unpleasant.
Food was good but the music was way to loud especially when trying to eat dinner
Great atmosphere, food, and service. Totally accommodating to allergy needs.
Amazing foods and service is great . Sat at the bar had a very enjoyable time .

Great place to meet a friend or two for drinks and or food. The drinks are great, and strong. The bartenders are amazing. But the food... the food is SOOOOO good! The cauliflower tacos were delicious. Multiple great options for vegan, gluten free, and carnivorous people. The live music was pretty good too. I will definitely be going back.
It's my safe haven for late night dinners. Food is not the best, but you won't hate it.

The food is absolutely disgusting, on top of being overpriced and faux fancy. Had to go to another restaurant afterwards, since the portions were so small. The waitress explained what a specials menu is (as if we didnt already know). Save your money and go to any other place on Moody St.
good food, drink, nice place for brunch
Great food

I have gone back many times because of their service and the atmosphere. Once they were a little overwhelmed and I asked to speak with the manger who could not have been nicer or more appreciative of my feedback. They have a first class staff.

Nice, friendly, attentive staff, would go back definitely. Interesting menu, food was very good 😁 There was a bunch of us coming in at different times and ordering late, they were very accommodating. They have parking behind them or you can use the parking behind the cinema which is also very close.
Very nice atmosphere. Friendly staff and attentive service. Try the truffle fries!
Friendly and great service. Well prepared

I hosted a private work function here for about 50 people. I found them to be extremely accommodating to any request i had.  We selected a variety of appetizers, however i found the short rib macaroni and cheese to be the favorite of the night. Our sit down dinner, went over extremely well. The filet and scallops were some of the best i'd had in recent years. Overall atmosphere was very relaxing, yet fun at the same time. Great spot to come together with friends and coworkers. Price was extremely reasonable for what we purchased. Will definitely be back for lunch some time.
Nice Place: We have been a few times, always good.

Came here for drinks after light dinner across the street 😉 Ended up getting cauliflower tacos for myself with a glass of tempranillo. Very tasty tacos! Could've been better with few pieces removed, but it was good! We sat at the bar and our waitress was very helpful. Would definitely return!

Excellent business to support. Family owned. Diverse menu. Very detailed garnishes, and fresh oysters. The service is unbeatable, and the location is convenient. Beats many Boston restaurants taste-wise, but with lower cost and more convenient parking. Great deals, great drinks, and impeccable meals.
Nice place I have only been at night to drink. Only one bathroom so the line was ridiculous but other than that it was good.
Lexi is the star waitress of this place. She made our NYE more enjoyable thanks to her effort and commitment.
My Warm Buddha Bowl was delicious with the addition of salmon.  The waitstaff was friendly and helpful.

Good food, great service. A little pricey but I'd go back.
Sat at the bar and ordered wine and burgers. Good selection of wine and the burger was cooked to perfection!
Great food and atmosphere!

This is the first time we've tried this place, and all I can say is that I don't know what to so long.  The menu is full of interesting choices (this is a breakfast/lunch/brunch restaurant) and it's going to take many visits to try everything that I want to.  The atmosphere is clean with pictures of Waltham throughout, and the wait staff were all peasant and friendly.

Review From 2/9/2016 One Word. Amazing.  Bistro781 is staple on the Moody Street scene; only opening in July 2015 This is without a doubt one of the best establishments I've ever been to.  my wife and I stopped in on Tuesday Night, and we were helped by Lauren, who was on point and so very helpful and knowledgeable about the menu. The restaurant itself had a nice atmosphere with low lighting and tables on one side, and a bar and tvs on the other side. Both restaurant and restrooms in establishment were very clean.  I ordered a delicious (but not for those who are dieting) Jalapeno Popper Burger, which was served with fries. This burger is deep fried, but don't let that push you away. It's served with fries (which were amazingly seasoned and crispy) and Texas Toast as a bun.  My Girlfriend had Tomato and Goat Cheese stuffed Chicken served with asparagus and a baked potato. The chicken was delicious and cooked perfectly.The only thing lacking on this dish was a bit more of the chicken gravy for use on the baked potato.  We ended dinner with a macaroon desert. This plate came with three macaroons; cheesecake, orange creme, and mint chocolate. It was a very attractive and sweet dish.  There is free parking for this restaurant as well. It is about two blocks down Gordon street. There's a big Bistro 781 sign and a huge lot.  Overall, I would recommend Bistro781 for it's food and service. I would definitely suggest this as a great place for a casual date, and prices are good; about 16-20$ a plate.

walked in one weekday lunch time and found the place empty, but welcoming. server seemed a bit...overloaded with tasks, but was very pleasant and attentive. shout out to the very kind server who went out of her way to make pink lemonade for the toddler diner!  blueprint of the space is long and deep. one side at the bar with multiple TVs, the other side with tables decorated with pictures of the town, partitioned by a short wall. some tall tables out by the front give a cocktail hour chilling the perfect setup.  husband found this place on an app that searches for gluten-free dining. kudos to them for having enough offerings that are naturally gluten free, along with some that can be made as such with accommodations.  food is delicious and well made; we all enjoyed the apps and our respective meal. could just be us with small stomach; there was enough leftover to make another person's meal.  only thing that baffles me is the pricing. for example, "small plates" range from $13 to $17 -- that's the range of an entree at any other place with the same calibre!  even our lunch dishes were in the same price range.  so...what exactly is the idea of "small plates"? for time being, i also thought that meant "apps for sharing", but the offerings within that category don't seem to suggest so. maybe they meant a slightly smaller portion or lighter meal choices.  another pricing baffle: kids meal pasta, $6. add shrimp +$8, add chicken +$5. what's with doubling the base price just by adding protein??? lucky our kid likes it plain anyway, so i didn't have to begrudgingly shell out $14 for a kid's meal.  pricing aside, it was a great meal. may return for the $1 oysters or brunch (starting in March, boo).  free one-hour street parking on the main road, or pull into Spruce St lot to park a couple hours ($1/2hr) to a day...I think there is that option.
